In SpriteBatch.cs->DrawInternal there are 2 lines of code at the bottom of the function that stop SpriteBatch from working correctly.

if (_sortMode == SpriteSortMode.Immediate)
  _batcher.DrawBatch(_sortMode);

Even though it is in immediate mode, it shouldn't draw immediately.

By commenting out these two lines of code the batcher will work correctly by batching draw calls. It increases 2D performance by a huge amount.

